chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you have a brain empyema.
chunks.plain_content:
Empyema (brain) and driving
You must tell DVLA if you have a brain empyema.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:

chunks.html_content: Fill in form B1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
